{
  "stem": "15962.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "But when I look at the number of family members who survived, it's really those who were able to escape the Holocaust who survived, not those who stayed behind.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Those were very few.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "My father was somewhat more resigned to fate.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And I recall a number of occasions of-- where his extreme pessimism came through.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Even a week or so before he was taken to the gas chambers, he was resigned to his fate, whereas my mother was always fighting to survive and hoping that, by some miracle, she will come back.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And, and the year or more when I was separated from my parents, I-- what, what kept me going was the belief that she will survive.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, if I may again go back a little bit, the deportations didn't start on December 15, 1942.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They started somewhat earlier.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There was a-- the ghetto Theresienstadt is, was a 18th century fortress named after Maria Theresa, the empress of-- the Habsburg empress of Austria.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "In that century, there were quite a few fortresses that had the typical star-shaped plan of fortifications and large barracks for troops.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The Germans moved out all the inhabitants and created that as the ghetto, because it was easily enclosed and guarded.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] I believe the first deportation took place in the-- in October, 1941, when the first transport of able-bodied young men was sent to prepare the barracks for future transport.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So all through this time, which was almost a year and a half, we were living in constant fear that we will be next to be, to be deported.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I guess that wasn't a, a known-- at least known, known to the population-- schedule of when our turn will come.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
